# PR Preparation Workflow

Invoke with: *"prepare PR"*, *"ready for review"*, *"PR checklist"*, *"before I submit"*

---

## 1. Code Completion

- [ ] All requirements met
- [ ] Edge cases handled
- [ ] Error scenarios covered
- [ ] No TODO comments without context
- [ ] No commented-out code
- [ ] No console.log / debug code

---

## 2. Quality Checks

### Run All Checks
```bash
npm run lint && npm run format:check && npm run knip && npm run typecheck && npm run test && npm run build
```

### Linting & Formatting
- [ ] ESLint passes (0 errors, 0 warnings)
- [ ] Prettier formatting clean
- [ ] Knip: no unused files, dependencies, or exports

### TypeScript
- [ ] No type errors in shared + server
- [ ] Client builds without errors (Vite)
- [ ] No implicit `any` types
- [ ] Shared types used (not duplicated)

### Tests
- [ ] All existing tests pass
- [ ] New tests added for new server code
- [ ] Edge cases tested

---

## 3. Self Review

### Developer
- [ ] Single responsibility followed
- [ ] No code duplication
- [ ] Consistent with existing patterns
- [ ] Zod schemas in shared (not duplicated)
- [ ] `validateBody` on all POST routes

### QE
- [ ] Loading/error/empty states in React pages
- [ ] External service failures handled (server)
- [ ] Null/undefined from API handled in UI
- [ ] Double-submit prevention on mutations

### Security
- [ ] Route params/body validated
- [ ] SQL uses parameterized queries
- [ ] No secrets in code or responses

### Monitoring Expert
- [ ] RP API calls handle pagination
- [ ] Zod schemas match actual data shapes
- [ ] Notifications don't block poll cycle

---

## 4. Monorepo-Specific

- [ ] Shared package built and exported
- [ ] No cross-package imports (client ↛ server)
- [ ] Types imported from `@cnv-monitor/shared`

---

## 5. Deployment

- [ ] K8s manifests updated if needed
- [ ] ConfigMap/Secret updated for new env vars
- [ ] Dockerfile works with changes
- [ ] CI pipeline will pass

---

## 6. Commit Hygiene

### Format
```
<type>: <short summary>

<description if needed>
```

Types: `feat`, `fix`, `refactor`, `chore`, `docs`

---

## 7. PR Description

```markdown
## Description
> Brief description of changes

## Changes
- packages/shared: Added/Modified X
- packages/server: Added/Modified Y
- packages/client: Added/Modified Z

## Testing
> How this was tested

## Configuration
> New environment variables or config changes
```

---

## 8. PR State Check

Before pushing to an existing PR branch or amending a commit:

1. **Check if the PR is still open**: `gh pr view <number> --json state -q '.state'`
2. If state is `MERGED` or `CLOSED`:
   - Do NOT push to the old branch
   - `git checkout main && git pull origin main`
   - Create a new branch from main
   - Apply changes and open a new PR
3. If state is `OPEN`: safe to push/amend

**Never push to a merged PR branch.**

---

## 9. Final Checklist

- [ ] `npm run typecheck` passes
- [ ] `npm run test` passes
- [ ] `npm run build` succeeds
- [ ] No debug code
- [ ] Self-reviewed
- [ ] Commits clean
- [ ] PR is still open (not merged) before pushing
